1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 26 MRSA §850-H, sub-§2, ¶A, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt. AAA,
3 §7, is repealed and the following enacted in its place:
4 A. If the private plan is in the form of self-insurance:
5 (1) The employer must furnish a bond to the State with a surety company
6 authorized to transact business in the State, in the form, amount and manner
7 required by the department; and
8 (2) The department may not allow the pooling of risk, financial resources or
9 administration among multiple employers;
10 Sec. 2. 26 MRSA §850-H, sub-§3, ¶E, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt. AAA,
11 §7, is amended to read:
12 E. Failure to submit reports or comply with other requirements as required by the
13 commissioner by rule; or
14 Sec. 3. 26 MRSA §850-H, sub-§3, ¶F, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt. AAA,
15 §7, is amended to read:
16 F. Failure to comply with this subchapter or the rules adopted pursuant to this
17 subchapter.; or
18 Sec. 4. 26 MRSA §850-H, sub-§3, ¶G is enacted to read:
19 G. In the case of a private plan in the form of self-insurance, the pooling of risk,
20 financial resources or administration among multiple employers.
21 Sec. 5. Retroactivity. Notwithstanding the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 1, section
22 302, this Act applies retroactively to April 1, 2025.
23 SUMMARY
2244 This bill clarifies that for a private plan in the form of self-insurance, the pooling of
2255 risk, financial resources or administration among multiple employers is prohibited under
2266 the paid family and medical leave benefits program. It also provides that this provision
2277 applies retroactively to April 1, 2025.
